<task id="151" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Gap B — Server-side EntityName lazy-fetch in PlaybookChatContextProvider per audit 120</title>
    <phase>Wave 12 — MVP Completion</phase>
    <wave>12</wave>
    <sub-wave>12.4</sub-wave>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>bff-api + code-impl; modifies system-prompt enrichment guard path</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>W12-4</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, assistant, wave12</tags>
    <estimated-effort>0.5-1 day</estimated-effort>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Audit 120 Gap B: `EntityName` is never populated by the SpaarkeAi client → `PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs:550` guard fails → system prompt enrichment is unconditionally skipped. Fix: when EntityName is missing but entityId+entityType are present, server-side lazy-fetch the entity's display name from Dataverse and populate EntityName before reaching the guard.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a BFF developer adding minimal server-side fallback logic. Add lazy-fetch only; do NOT change client-side or the guard's semantics.
  </role>

  <goal>
System prompt enrichment fires when client sends entityType + entityId (even when EntityName missing). Assistant chat in matter context has matter-aware system prompt. Combined with T150's naming normalization, audit Scenario A passes.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Audit notes: projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-120-assistant-workspace.md (Gap B at PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs:550)
    - Existing service: IGenericEntityService for Dataverse reads
    - Cache opportunity: per-request memoize (don't re-fetch same entity twice in single request lifecycle)
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Per CLAUDE.md §10 + §11: modification only; reuse IGenericEntityService; no new abstractions
    - Per ADR-038: integration-heavy tests; mock IGenericEntityService at boundary
    - MUST not block on the lazy-fetch — if Dataverse times out / errors, log + fall back to original guard behavior (skip enrichment); don't fail the chat request
    - Cache scope: per-request (avoid leaking state across requests; avoid stale data)
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-120-assistant-workspace.md (Gap B section)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.3)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs (Gap B at line 550)
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Dataverse/IGenericEntityService.cs
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Read PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs:540-570 context** (15 min) — understand the existing guard
2. **Identify normalized entityType + entityId source post-T150** (15 min)
3. **Implement lazy-fetch** (45-60 min):
   - When EntityName empty AND entityType + entityId present: call IGenericEntityService to fetch entity's display name (typically `name` or entity-specific primary name field)
   - Populate EntityName before guard
   - If fetch fails: log + skip enrichment (preserve original guard behavior)
4. **Add per-request cache** (15-20 min) to avoid duplicate fetches
5. **Add unit tests** (45 min) per ADR-038:
   - Test: missing EntityName + present entityType/Id → fetch + enrich succeeds
   - Test: Dataverse fetch fails → graceful skip (no enrichment, no chat failure)
   - Test: cached entry on second call within same request
6. **Build + test verification** (15 min)

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read / Grep / Glob
    - Edit
    - Bash (dotnet test, dotnet build)
    - TodoWrite
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs (M) — lazy-fetch added
    - Unit test additions
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] Lazy-fetch implemented in PlaybookChatContextProvider
    - [ ] Per-request cache prevents duplicate fetches
    - [ ] Fetch failure gracefully degrades (skip enrichment; chat request still succeeds)
    - [ ] Unit tests cover success + failure + cache hit
    - [ ] `dotnet test` 0 new failures
    - [ ] `dotnet build` 0 errors
    - [ ] No new packages / DI registrations
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
